column6: Athletic Center University of Toronto
column7: Indoor gym with indoor swimming pool, sports medicine physicians available to athletes

column6: Densgrove Park
column7: Very large quiet field to read a book alone or spend time with family. A small playground and two baseball fields for children and families to spend time together.

column6: Royal Ontario Museum
column7: The Royal Ontario Museum (ROM) provides free general admission on Tuesdays for all full-time students attending a postsecondary institution. A current student ID is required.

column6: Davenport Perth Neighbourhood and Community Health Centre - Health Clinic
column7: The Davenport Perth Health Centre provides primary care for clients using a multi-disciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nurse-practitioners, counsellor/therapists, dietitians and medical administration staff. The health services offered by DPNCHC are restricted to those living in the catchment area.

column6: Office of Health Professions Student Affairs
column7: Provides personal and couples counseling and career decision advice to health professional students

column6: Ryerson Recreation and Athletics Center
column7: Facility for intramurals, open recreation, sports clubs, badminton, basketball, soccer & volleyball

column6: Sorauren Farmer's Market
column7: A family friendly market in Sorauren Park. Fresh and local produce available. Great place to stroll, socialize, and learn about healthy and sustainable eating!

column6: Sunshine Wholesome Market
column7: This health food store has it all! They sell numerous types of fresh immune-booting juices and smoothies, excellent for when you are feeling sick. They also have healthy prepared foods, as well as the possibility to customize your own healthy salad. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable.

column6: Mattamy Athletic Centre
column7: cardio room, free weights as well as a wide variety of machine weights and a sprung hardwood dance studio

column6: Mt Pleasant Cemetery
column7: Beautiful walking and running trails; Saturday evening concerts during the summer

column6: Trinity Bellwoods Park
column7: Trinity Bellwoods Park is a large, green space so you can always find a place to sit and chill, just read or engage in physical activity. It's relaxing and free. There are also (flea) markets on the weekends, that I know of the in summer (not sure about fall/winter) and sometimes you can find really great books for just $1 or $2!

column6: Trinity Bellwoods Park-Dog Bowl
column7: Play with and pet dogs for all-day for free! Nice hillside view of Trinity Bellwoods Park. Peaceful and quiet. Take a book, a coffee, or a friend.
